        "Building REST APIs with PHP",
        "REST APIs allow different software systems to communicate over HTTP. In this guide, we walk through creating a RESTful API using PHP and MySQL, covering endpoints, request methods, and JSON responses.\n\nWhat is REST?\n\nREST (Representational State Transfer) is an architectural style for designing networked applications. It relies on stateless, client-server communication using standard HTTP methods. RESTful APIs have become the standard way for web and mobile applications to communicate with backend servers.\n\nHTTP Methods and Their Purposes\n\nGET retrieves resources without modifying them. POST creates new resources. PUT updates an entire resource, while PATCH applies partial modifications. DELETE removes a resource. Each method maps to a CRUD operation, making APIs intuitive and predictable.\n\nDesigning Your API Endpoints\n\nFollow RESTful conventions: use nouns for resource names (e.g., /api/users, /api/posts), use HTTP methods to define actions, and nest related resources logically (e.g., /api/users/5/posts). Return appropriate HTTP status codes — 200 for success, 201 for created, 404 for not found, and 500 for server errors.\n\nImplementation with PHP\n\nStart by reading the request method with \$_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD'] and parsing the URL path. Use a simple router to direct requests to the appropriate handler function. Parse JSON request bodies with json_decode(file_get_contents('php://input')). Return responses with json_encode() and proper Content-Type headers.\n\nAuthentication and Security\n\nProtect your API with authentication — token-based authentication (like JWT) is widely used. Validate and sanitize all input data. Implement rate limiting to prevent abuse. Use HTTPS in production to encrypt data in transit. Add CORS headers to control which domains can access your API.\n\nTesting Your API\n\nUse tools like Postman, Insomnia, or cURL to test your endpoints. Write automated tests to verify each endpoint returns the expected responses for valid and invalid inputs.",
