        "CSS Grid Layout Masterclass",
        "CSS Grid is a powerful two-dimensional layout system that revolutionizes how we build web page layouts. Discover how to create complex, responsive layouts with minimal code.\n\nThe Evolution of CSS Layouts\n\nWeb layouts have evolved from table-based designs in the 1990s, through float-based layouts in the 2000s, to Flexbox in the 2010s. CSS Grid, introduced in 2017, represents the most significant advancement yet — it is the first CSS module designed specifically for creating two-dimensional layouts.\n\nGrid vs Flexbox\n\nWhile Flexbox excels at one-dimensional layouts (either a row or a column), CSS Grid handles two-dimensional layouts (rows AND columns simultaneously). They are complementary tools: use Grid for the overall page structure and Flexbox for components within grid areas.\n\nGetting Started with Grid\n\nApply display: grid to a container element. Define columns with grid-template-columns and rows with grid-template-rows. The fr unit distributes available space proportionally — for example, grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr creates three columns where the middle one is twice as wide.\n\nThe Power of grid-template-areas\n\nOne of Grid's most elegant features is named grid areas. You can visually define your layout in CSS using a text-based map:\n\ngrid-template-areas:\n  \"header header header\"\n  \"sidebar main aside\"\n  \"footer footer footer\";\n\nThis creates an intuitive, readable layout definition that maps directly to your HTML structure.\n\nResponsive Grids\n\nCombine Grid with media queries for responsive layouts, or use auto-fill and auto-fit with minmax() for intrinsically responsive grids that adapt without breakpoints: grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)).\n\nAdvanced Techniques\n\nExplore implicit grids, grid-auto-flow for automatic placement, spanning items across multiple rows or columns, and alignment utilities like justify-items, align-items, and place-content for precise control over every element in your grid.",
